ON UBUNTU 12.04

sudo apt-get install unzip
sudo apt-get install apache2
sudo apt-get install php5
sudo apt-get install libapache2-mod-php5
sudo /etc/init.d/apache2 restart
Note that if apache is already installed you can omit the first line. Your web files will now be found in /var/www/

Q: First php page?
rm -rf /var/www/index.html

cat > /var/www/index.php <<EOT
<?php

print_r (phpinfo());

?>
EOT

http://localhost

#-----------------------------------------------------------------------
# SYSTEM REQUIREMENT
#-----------------------------------------------------------------------

Q: SOFTWARE requirement?
    PHP >= 5.3.7
    MCrypt PHP Extension


Q: HARDWARE requirement => Composer issue during installation ?
https://github.com/composer/composer/issues/945
Had the same issue when trying to do a deployment to an Amazon AWS EC2 Micro instance. 
These instances have only 613MB of memory in total so composer fails to allocate enough memory for an update to run. 
Upgrading to a Small instance with 1.7GB of total memory got rid of the issue.

Q: Laravel requires the Mcrypt PHP extension. ?
php -m
the PHP module is not found/installed.

#-----------------------------------------------------------------------
# FROM DOWNLOAD
#-----------------------------------------------------------------------

1/  Download Laravel
    sudo curl -S https://codeload.github.com/laravel/laravel/zip/master -o /usr/local/src/laravel-master.zip
2/  Extract the Laravel archive and upload the contents to your web server.
    cd /var/www; unzip /usr/local/src/laravel-master.zip
    firefox http://localhost/laravel-master             # <-- you should see the files
3/ Install dependencies
    sudo sh -c "curl -sS https://getcomposer.org/installer | php -- --install-dir=/usr/local/src
    sudo cp /usr/local/src/composer.phar /usr/local/bin/composer                                        # <-- PHAR files are PHP ARCHIVES
    sudo /usr/local/bin/composer install 
    
3/  Set the value of the key option in the config/application.php file to a random, 32 character string.
4/  Verify that the storage/views directory is writable.
        You can use chmod option like this
        #chmod a+w your_path/storage/views  -R
5/    Navigate to your application in a web browser. http://localhost/laravel/public

#-----------------------------------------------------------------------
# USING COMPOSER
#-----------------------------------------------------------------------

1/  Download composer (used to install laravel)
    sudo sh -c "curl -sS https://getcomposer.org/installer | php -- --install-dir=/usr/local/src"
    sudo cp /usr/local/src/composer.phar /usr/local/bin/composer
    
2/  Download Laravel
    composer create-project laravel/laravel
    ---
php composer.phar create-project laravel/laravel
